\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CubemapArray"},{"type":"text","text":", which are texture arrays with specialized cubemap functions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A Texture2DArray is also different from an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AtlasTexture"},{"type":"text","text":": In a Texture2DArray, all images are treated separately. In an atlas, the regions (i.e. the single images) can be of different sizes. Furthermore, you usually need to add a padding around the regions, to prevent accidental UV mapping to more than one region. The same goes for mipmapping: Mipmap chains are handled separately for each layer. In an atlas, the slicing has to be done manually in the fragment shader."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create such a texture file yourself, reimport your image files using the Godot Editor import presets."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/texture2darray"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A single texture resource which consists of multiple, separate images. Each image has the same dimensions and number of mipmap levels."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2DArray","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Texture2DArray/createPlaceholder()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2DArray\/createPlaceholder()","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/texture2darray\/createplaceholder()","title":"createPlaceholder()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func